import React from "react"
import { Link } from "react-router-dom"
import { BrowserRouter as Router, Routes, Route } from 'react-router-dom';

import Tide from "./Tide"
import Weather from "./Weather"
import Home from "./Home"


function App(props) {

  function handleClick(event) {
    event.preventDefault()
    axios.get(`https://api.weather.gov/points/${coordinates.latitude},${coordinates.longitude}`)
      .then(response => {
        setXcoord(response.data.properties.gridX)
        setYcoord(response.data.properties.gridY)
        console.log(xCoord, yCoord)
        coordinates.latitude = ""
        coordinates.longitude = ""

      })
      .catch(error => console.log(error))

  }

  return (
    <Router>
      <nav>
        <Link to="/">Home</Link>
        <Link to="/weather">Weather</Link>
        <Link to="/tide">Tide</Link>

      </nav>
      <Routes>
        <Route path="/" element={<Home />} />
        <Route path="tide" element={<Tide handleClick />} />
        <Route path="weather" element={<Weather />} />
      </Routes>
    </Router>
  )
}

export default App
